      "content": "it's just that the more i try, the more i realize i'm just fundamentally different. like, it's not even a matter of learning \"social skills\" or whatever... it's just a wall. i look at everyone else just existing effortlessly and i feel like an alien watching them from the outside. it feels like i'm stuck in a loop of suffering that has no actual exit. everything is just so loud and heavy all the time.",
